    </content>
    <content lang="en">
      <city>Bern</city>
      <title>SERI News, October 17</title>
      <lead>Information from the State Secretariat for Education, Research and Innovation SERI: Vocational qualifications for adults: results of two studies / Swiss Science Prize Marcel Benoist / swissnex: new name, new projects and new face</lead>
      <text link="no">&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Second National Stakeholders Conference on International Cooperation in Vocational and Professional Education and Training (IC-VPET)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;IC-VPET Opportunities – Priorities, Paths and Perspectives&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vocational qualifications for adults: results of two studies now available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The most successful outcomes are when both employees and employers are convinced of the benefits&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;‘Strengthening the Federal Vocational Baccalaureate’ project: Interim results and outlook&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;More flexible options and better communication&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Direct federal subsidy for individuals taking preparatory courses for federal professional examinations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Quick explanation of the new federal subject-based subsidy&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aptitude test for studies in medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Critical analysis of a twenty-year-old tool&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Swiss Science Prize Marcel Benoist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Climate researcher Thomas Stocker receives this year’s award&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;European XFEL X-ray laser opened in Hamburg&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A new beacon of international research cooperation&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A very eventful year for the swissnex network&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;New name, new projects and new faces&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</text>
      <contact>info@sbfi.admin.ch</contact>
